wikipedia_page.main: A. Wilcocks was a Cornish rugby union player who competed in the 1908 Summer Olympics at White City Stadium, London. He also played for Plymouth Albion R.F.C. and 14 times for Cornwall. He was a member of the British rugby union team, which on 26 October 1908 won the Olympic silver medal for Great Britain. He played Rugby League for Oldham, and retired there.
